  11:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  * This implementation of kalman filter can dynamically adjust dimension and
  12:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  * value of matrix H R and K according to the measurement validity under any
  13:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  * circumstance that the sampling rate of component sensors are different.
  14:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  *
  15:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  * ه› و­¤çں©éکµHه’ŒRçڑ„هˆ‌ه§‹هŒ–ن¼ڑن¸ژçں©éکµP Aه’ŒQوœ‰و‰€ن¸چهگŒم€‚هڈ¦ه¤–çڑ„ï¼Œهœ¨هˆ‌ه§‹هŒ–é‡ڈوµ‹هگ‘
  16:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  * ه…¥ن¼ و„ںه™¨é‡ڈوµ‹و‰€ه¯¹ه؛”çڑ„çٹ¶و€پن¸ژè؟™ن¸ھé‡ڈوµ‹çڑ„و–¹ه¼ڈï¼Œè¯¦وƒ…è¯·è§پن¾‹ç¨‹
  17:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  * Therefore, the initialization of matrix P, F, and Q is sometimes different
  18:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  * from that of matrices H R. when initialization. Additionally, the corresponding
  19:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  * state and the method of the measurement should be provided when initializing
  20:modules/algorithm/kalman_filter.c ****  * measurement vector z. For more details, please see the example.
